# <%= Conf.texFont.name %> fonts

This CTAN package contains the fonts used by the <%= Conf.texFont.name %> project.

To install these fonts locally cd to either the global texmf-local 
directory OR to your personal texmf directory.

Then unzip this CTAN package.  This should place the required files 
into appropriate directories.

Then in the same texmf-local or texmf directory edit the file:

> web2c/updmap-local.cfg

by adding the single line:

> Map <%= Conf.texFont.texFonts.fontName %>.map

Then run

> tlmgr generate updmap

once.

Then run

> mktexlsr
> updmap-sys

to update the font maps for all the other output tools (dvips, pdflate, 
etc)

